  "prompt": "What is voltage regulation formula?",
  "response": "Voltage regulation is a measure of how well a power system, transformer, or electrical machine can maintain a constant voltage level under varying load conditions. The formula for voltage regulation is given by:\n\n\\[ \\text{Voltage Regulation} (\\%) = \\frac{V_{no-load} - V_{full-load}}{V_{full-load}} \\times 100 \\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( V_{no-load} \\) is the voltage when there is no load (or very light load) connected to the system.\n- \\( V_{full-load} \\) is the voltage when the system is operating at its full load capacity.\n\nThis formula calculates the percentage drop in voltage from no-load to full-load conditions. A lower percentage indicates better voltage regulation, meaning the system maintains a more stable voltage as the load changes.",
